description:
This is a nice children's book full of color illustrations. Many of the illustrations contain dialogue bubbles making it very much like a comic book.

It contains the following stories:

Brer Rabbit's Frolic

Brother Bear's Big House

Brer Rabbit Treats the Creeturs to a Race

Brer Rabbit's Flying Trip

Brer Rabbit and the Gold Mine

Brer Rabbit gets Brer Fox a Hoss

Brer Rabbit Finds the Moon in the Mill Pond

How Mr. Lion Lost His Wool

How Brer Rabbit Got a House

Brer Rabbit and the Partridge Nest

In this issue:

"Taken Under: Chapter One: A Faint Smell of Violets" by Debra Rodia and Michael Lark

"Scratchin' " by Brian McDonald and Ron McCain Jr.

"To Reach the Wall" by Roland Mann, Ken H. Branch and Steven D. Butler

"Sketchbook" by Mark Winfrey

"The Crowded Street" by William Cullen Bryant and Richard G. Taylor

"Go-Man: All Rise (Chapter Three)" by Bill Widener and Heather Kennedy

"Caliber Bonus: The Mechanoids (Preview)" by Gary Reed and Mark Winfrey

Koni Konfidential tells the tale of Koni Kanawai, a recent transfer student who soon finds out that Hawaii is more than just beautiful beaches and exotic scenery. There's a dark side to the island that is not seen in the usual tourist spots. It's mystical and paranormal. Along with her new friends, Pete, Krystal, and Logan, Koni explores the supernatural mysteries at Honolulu High.

Note: The digital edition (3/13/2013) for this graphic novel was released two weeks earlier then the print edition (3/31/2013).
name: GN

description: Johnny Boo has been eating a little too much ice cream, and now his muscles have gotten all floppy and droopy. Meanwhile, the Ice Cream Monster has changed his ways and now has big strong muscles, thanks to his new favorite food: apples! Terribly embarrassed by his own puny muscles, Johnny Boo sets out on a quest to find some happy apples that can give him strong happy muscles. But it won't be easy - especially if the Ice Cream Monster mistakes him for a delicious ice cream cone!
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Johnny Boo and the Happy Apples

description:
THE GODLAND SAGA CONTINUES! As Commander Adam Archer begins to understand his galactic destiny, more secrets are revealed to him, including the origin of the universe and the mystery behind Iboga! A truly surreal collection of mind-bending stories featuring all-new adversaries like the Tormentor, King Janus and the Never! Not to mention fan-favorite baddies, Basil Cronus and Friedrich Nickelhead! Forget about any other so-called "cosmic" comics out there - GODLAND is the 21st Century original!

Also includes a humorous holiday short, starring Basil Cronus!

Collects Godland #7-12.
name: Vol. 2: Another Sunny Delight

description:
Finally! The stupendous and gripping climax of the Triad's rampage on Earth! The Eisner-nominated GØDLAND saga reaches a fever pitch in this fourth trade paperback collection, regaling you with the continuing exploits of Earth's emissary to the cosmos: Commander Adam Archer. The cold hand of death touches friends and foes alike, with the fate of the Earth at stake! You can't miss this one! (and, yeah, Basil's still sporting a woman's body!)

Collects Godland #19-24.
name: Vol. 4: Amplified Now!

description:
The Eisner-nominated GØDLAND saga continues into this fifth softcover volume of mayhem! Follow Earth's emissary to the cosmos, Commander Adam Archer, as he journeys into deep space in search of his sister, Neela. On his journey, he meets cosmic Vikings, Leviticus and Vayikra - and does battle with the otherworldly weirdness of N'ull Pax Mizer and R@d-Ur Rezz! All this, and the return of Friedrich Nickelhead in his grandest scheme ever!

Collects Godland #25-30.
name: Vol. 5: Far Beyond the Bang!

description:
From the burning heart of a pocket dimension to the farthest reaches of our own reality, the saga of GØDLAND continues in this third trade paperback collection! As cosmic forces of evil conspire against the Earth and all who inhabit it, its lone emissary to the stars - Commander Adam Archer - finds himself the target of humanity's mistrust and deceit. All this, and Basil still wears the body of a woman!

Collects Godland #13-18.
name: Vol. 3: Proto Plastic Party

description:
This is how it all began! The cosmic superhero epic is back and this collection is chock-full of all the "cosmic" you could ask for! Experience the glory of Commander Adam Archer, the enigmatic alien Maxim, the wacky Basil Cronus, the evil Discordia, the confusing Freidrich Nickelhead and that's just scratching the surface! If you want cosmic, we've got cosmic!

Collects Godland #1-6.
name: Vol. 1: Hello, Cosmic!
